    {
      "id": "cli-nb:1f41e80383",
      "hintSrcLang": "en",
      "variants": {
        "en": [
          {
            "text": "kapi helps you manage multilingual content — convert document formats,\ntranslate with AI, and run quality checks across a wide range of file types."
          }
        ],
        "nb": [
          {
            "text": "kapi hjelper deg å håndtere flerspråklig innhold — konverter dokumentformater,\noversett med AI og kjør kvalitetskontroller på et bredt utvalg filtyper."
          }
        ]
      },
      "created": "2026-06-11T08:02:59Z",
      "updated": "2026-06-11T08:02:59Z"
    },
    {
      "id": "cli-nb:1f4c25bb8d",
      "hintSrcLang": "en",
      "variants": {
        "en": [
          {
            "text": "Manage translation memory.\n\nA translation memory (TM) stores previously translated segments as a SQLite\ndatabase. Use these commands to import/export TMX, look up matches, and manage\nTM entries.\n\nResource location (mutually exclusive):\n  --name <n>      Named TM in KAPI_HOME (~/.config/kapi/tm/<n>.db)\n  --local         TM in current directory (./tm.db)\n  --file <path>   Explicit file path\n\nDefault (no flag): same as --local (uses ./tm.db)."
          }
        ],
        "nb": [
          {
            "text": "Administrer oversettelsesminne.\n\nEt oversettelsesminne (TM) lagrer tidligere oversatte segmenter som en\nSQLite-database. Bruk disse kommandoene til å importere/eksportere TMX, slå opp\ntreff og administrere TM-enheter.\n\nRessursplassering (gjensidig utelukkende):\n  --name <n>      Navngitt TM i KAPI_HOME (~/.config/kapi/tm/<n>.db)\n  --local         TM i gjeldende katalog (./tm.db)\n  --file <path>   Eksplisitt filsti\n\nStandard (uten flagg): samme som --local (bruker ./tm.db)."
          }
        ]
      },
      "created": "2026-06-11T08:02:59Z",
      "updated": "2026-06-11T08:02:59Z"
    },
    {
      "id": "cli-nb:204fdceaa2",
      "hintSrcLang": "en",
      "variants": {
        "en": [
          {
            "text": "Install a plugin from a registry. The plugin is downloaded,\nverified (SHA-256 + cosign signature), and unpacked into\n$XDG_DATA_HOME/kapi/plugins/<name>/.\n\nExamples:\n  kapi plugin install bowrain\n  kapi plugin install bowrain@^1.0\n  kapi plugin install bowrain --channel beta"
          }
        ],
        "nb": [
          {
            "text": "Installer et tillegg fra et register. Tillegget lastes ned,\nverifiseres (SHA-256 + cosign-signatur) og pakkes ut i\n$XDG_DATA_HOME/kapi/plugins/<name>/.\n\nEksempler:\n  kapi plugin install bowrain\n  kapi plugin install bowrain@^1.0\n  kapi plugin install bowrain --channel beta"
          }
        ]
      },
      "created": "2026-06-11T08:02:59Z",
      "updated": "2026-06-11T08:02:59Z"
    },
    {
      "id": "cli-nb:2093a70702",
      "hintSrcLang": "en",
      "variants": {
        "en": [
          {
            "text": "Update an installed plugin in place using the channel and constraint\nrecorded at install time. Pass --channel or --constraint to switch\ntracks during update; --index points the update at a different\nregistry index URL.\n\nExamples:\n  kapi plugin update bowrain\n  kapi plugin update bowrain --channel beta\n  kapi plugin update bowrain --constraint ^2.0"
          }
        ],
        "nb": [
          {
            "text": "Oppdater et installert tillegg på stedet med kanalen og versjonskravet\nsom ble registrert ved installasjon. Bruk --channel eller --constraint for å\nbytte spor under oppdateringen; --index peker oppdateringen mot en annen\nregisterindeks-URL.\n\nEksempler:\n  kapi plugin update bowrain\n  kapi plugin update bowrain --channel beta\n  kapi plugin update bowrain --constraint ^2.0"
          }
        ]
      },
      "created": "2026-06-11T08:02:59Z",
      "updated": "2026-06-11T08:02:59Z"
    },
    {
      "id": "cli-nb:24b3ed409a",
